  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&dhpackage;</refname>

    <refpurpose> a TV viewer for the Gnome environment.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&dhpackage;</command>

	<arg><option>-b, --bpp</option><replaceable>[=BPP]</replaceable></arg>
	<arg><option>-d, --debug</option></arg>
	<arg><option>--no-vbi</option></arg>
	<arg><option>-n, --tunerless-norm</option><replaceable>[=NORM]</replaceable></arg>
	<arg><option>--device</option><replaceable>[=DEVICE]</replaceable></arg>
	<arg><option>-v, --no-xv</option></arg>
	<arg><option>--dword-align</option></arg>
	<arg><option>-c, --command</option><replaceable>[=CMD]</replaceable></arg>
	<arg><option>-z, --no-zsfb</option></arg>
	<arg><option>-y, --yuv-format</option><replaceable>[=PIXFORMAT]</replaceable></arg>
	<arg><option>--console-errors</option></arg>

    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>

    <para><command>&dhpackage;</command> is a TV viewer, so displaying TV is
      its main goal. Nevertheless, there are a number of things that can be
      done to a image stream, and Zapping provides a way to do them, you
      just need a plug-in that fits your particular needs. If such a plug-in
      doesn't exist, you are encouraged to write one.</para>

  </refsect1>

 <refsect1>
    <title>OPTIONS</title>

    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-b</option>
          <option>--bpp=BPP</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Color depth of the X display.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-d</option>
          <option>--debug</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Set debug messages on.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-n</option>
          <option>--tunerless-norm=NORM</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Set the default standard/norm for tunerless inputs.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--device=DEVICE</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Video device to use.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-v</option>
          <option>--no-xv</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Disable XVideo extension support.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--dword-align</option></term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Force dword aligning of the overlay window.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-c</option>
          <option>--command=CMD</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Execute the given command and exit.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-z</option>
          <option>--no-zsfb</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Do not call zapping_setup_fb on startup.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>-y</option>
          <option>--yuv-format=PIXFORMAT</option>
        </term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Pixformat for XVideo capture mode [YUYV | YVU420].</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term><option>--console-errors</option></term>
        <listitem>
	  <para>Redirect the error messages to the console.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1>
    <title>AUTHOR</title>

    <para>This manual page was written by &dhusername; &dhemail; for
      the &debian; system (but may be used by others).</para>

  </refsect1>
